The paper deals with the problem of allocating finite inventories to heterogeneous customers arriving sequentially, which is a problem in game theory (cs.GT) and involves data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses online matching, advertising, and assortment problems, which are topics in information retrieval (cs.IR) and market analysis (cs.MA).
